import numpy as np
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

nums = np.arange(110)
plt.figure(figsize=(20, 25))
plt.suptitle('Our First Plot', fontsize=30)

plt.subplot(4, 2, 1)
plt.title('X', fontweight='bold')
plt.plot(nums, nums, color='blue')

plt.subplot(4, 2, 2)
plt.title('X squared', fontweight='bold')
plt.plot(nums, nums**2, color='red')

plt.subplot(4, 2, 3)
plt.title('X cubed', fontweight='bold')
plt.plot(nums, nums**3, color='magenta')

plt.subplot(4, 2, 4)
plt.title('Cos X', fontweight='bold')
plt.plot(nums, np.cos(nums), color='#6F1E51')

plt.subplot(4, 2, 5)
plt.title('Sin X', fontweight='bold')
plt.plot(nums, np.sin(nums), color='#ED4C67')

plt.subplot(4, 2, 6)
plt.title('tan X', fontweight='bold')
plt.plot(nums, np.tan(nums), color='#12CBC4')

plt.subplot(4, 2, 7)
plt.title('log X', fontweight='bold')
plt.plot(nums[1:], np.log(nums[1:]), color='#009432')

plt.subplot(4, 2, 8)
plt.title('ln X', fontweight='bold')
plt.plot(nums[1:], np.log2(nums[1:]), color='#D980FA')

plt.tight_layout(pad=5.0)
plt.show()
